.SH NAME
ga68 \- A GCC\-based compiler for Algol 68
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
ga68 [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-S\fR] [\fB\-g\fR] [\fB\-pg\fR]
     [\fB\-O\fR\fIlevel\fR] [\fB\-W\fR\fIwarn\fR...]
     [\fB\-I\fR\fIdir\fR...] [\fB\-L\fR\fIdir\fR...]
     [\fB\-f\fR\fIoption\fR...] [\fB\-m\fR\fImachine\-option\fR...]
     [\fB\-o\fR \fIoutfile\fR] [@\fIfile\fR] \fIinfile\fR...
.PP
Only the most useful options are listed here; see below for the
remainder.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
The \fBga68\fR command is the GNU compiler for the Algol 68 language and
supports many of the same options as \fBgcc\fR.  
This manual only documents the options specific to \fBga68\fR.
